The Senzo Meyiwa murder trial has been full of unexpected turns, much of them involving defence advocate Malesela Teffo. Earlier this afternoon he delivered another shock. He announced he is withdrawing from the case and will no longer be representing accused one to four. eNCA speaks to legal expert Zola Majavu. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - There’s been no end to the drama in the Senzo Meyiwa murder trial. Defence lawyer Malesela Teffo shocked the court when he withdrew as counsel for accused one to four. WATCH: Adv Teffo withdraws as counsel in Meyiwa murder trial He claims he’s been harassed by the police and state. Legal expert Zola Majavu says Teffo's handling of the matter is inexcusable. WATCH: Adv Teffo quits Meyiwa trial “If you’re aggrieved or your client is aggrieved there are other processes that you can follow. To accuse the judge is in poor taste," Majavu said. "You don’t do that as a defense council. What he did is unacceptable and inexcusable. There was no basis for the rant. It was bound to fail from the beginning.”